      <section id="what-is-vpn" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What is a VPN?</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          A <strong>Virtual Private Network (VPN)</strong> is a secure tunnel between your device and the internet that encrypts your data and masks your IP address. When you connect to a VPN server, your internet traffic is routed through an encrypted connection, making it virtually impossible for third parties—including your <abbr title="Internet Service Provider">ISP</abbr>, hackers, or government agencies—to monitor your online activities.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
          <p class="text-gray-800 font-medium mb-2"><strong>🔒 Simple Definition:</strong></p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Think of a VPN like sending mail in a locked box instead of a postcard. While the mail carrier (your ISP) still delivers it, they can't see what's inside. Your destination address (websites you visit) is also hidden—they only see the address of the VPN server.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          To fully understand VPNs, you need to know <a href="/education/history-of-vpn" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">how VPN technology evolved</a> from military applications to consumer privacy tools, and <a href="/education/why-need-vpn" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">why online privacy matters</a> more than ever in 2025.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="how-vpn-works" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">How VPNs Work: Technical Breakdown</h2>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Encryption Process</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          VPNs use military-grade encryption algorithms like <strong>AES-256</strong> or <strong>ChaCha20</strong> to scramble your data. Here's the step-by-step process:
        </p>

        <ol class="space-y-4 mb-8">
          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Data Encryption:</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Your device encrypts all outgoing data using the VPN client software before it leaves your computer.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Secure Tunneling:</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Encrypted data travels through a secure "tunnel" to the VPN server. This tunnel prevents anyone (including your ISP) from seeing the actual content.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">IP Address Masking:</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">The VPN server assigns you a new IP address from its location, completely hiding your real IP and physical location.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Web Request Forwarding:</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">The VPN server forwards your request to the destination website on your behalf. The website only sees the VPN server's IP address.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Response Routing:</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Data returns encrypted through the same secure tunnel back to your device, where it's decrypted.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 text-green-400 rounded-lg p-6 my-6 overflow-x-auto">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">VPN Handshake Process:</p>
          <pre class="text-sm"><code>Client Hello → Server Hello
→ Certificate Exchange (X.509)
→ Key Exchange (RSA-2048 or ECDH-P256)
→ Encrypted Tunnel Established (AES-256-GCM)
→ All traffic encrypted with ephemeral session keys
→ Perfect Forward Secrecy maintained</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="vpn-protocols" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">VPN Protocols Explained</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          VPN protocols determine how data is encrypted and transmitted. Here are the most common protocols in 2025:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-600 bg-blue-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">WireGuard (Recommended)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Speed:</strong> ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡ | <strong>Security:</strong> 🔒🔒🔒🔒🔒
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Modern, lightweight protocol with only ~4,000 lines of code (vs OpenVPN's 70,000+). Uses ChaCha20 encryption and offers the fastest speeds with strong security. Adopted by <a href="/reviews/mullvad" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Mullvad</a>, <a href="/reviews/ivpn" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">IVPN</a>, and most privacy-focused VPNs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-green-600 bg-green-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">OpenVPN</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Speed:</strong> ⚡⚡⚡ | <strong>Security:</strong> 🔒🔒🔒🔒🔒
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Open-source industry standard since 2001. Highly configurable with AES-256 encryption. Slower than WireGuard but extremely reliable and works on any port (great for bypassing firewalls).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-600 bg-purple-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">IKEv2/IPsec</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Speed:</strong> ⚡⚡⚡⚡ | <strong>Security:</strong> 🔒🔒🔒🔒
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Excellent for mobile devices. Quickly reconnects when switching between Wi-Fi and cellular. Native support on iOS and Android.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-red-600 bg-red-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">PPTP (Avoid)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Speed:</strong> ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡ | <strong>Security:</strong> 🔒 (Broken)
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Fast but completely broken security. Can be cracked by the NSA and other agencies. Never use PPTP for privacy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-6">
          <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Use WireGuard for best performance, or OpenVPN if maximum compatibility is needed. See our <a href="/education/vpn-protocols" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">complete protocol comparison guide</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="why-need-vpn" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why You Need a VPN in 2025</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🕵️</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">ISP Tracking</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Your ISP logs every website you visit and can sell this data to advertisers. In the US, ISPs can legally sell your browsing history thanks to the 2017 repeal of FCC privacy rules.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🌍</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Geo-Restrictions</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Access content blocked in your region. Stream Netflix libraries from other countries, access blocked news sites, or use services unavailable in your location.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">☕</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Public Wi-Fi Security</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Hackers can easily intercept data on public Wi-Fi networks at cafes, airports, and hotels. A VPN encrypts your connection, making it unreadable to attackers.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🏛️</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Government Surveillance</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Mass surveillance programs like PRISM and Five Eyes collect internet data. VPNs (especially in privacy-friendly jurisdictions) help protect against dragnet surveillance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-6">
          <p class="text-gray-800">
            <strong>⚠️ 2025 Context:</strong> With increased data retention laws in the EU, expanded surveillance powers in the UK (Investigatory Powers Act), and ongoing debates about encryption backdoors, VPNs have become essential privacy tools, not just for tech enthusiasts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="choosing-vpn" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">How to Choose the Right VPN</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Not all VPNs are created equal. Here's what to look for:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-500 text-xl">✓</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Verified No-Logs Policy:</strong> Look for independent audits by firms like Cure53 or KPMG. <a href="/reviews/mullvad" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Mullvad</a> and <a href="/reviews/ivpn" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">IVPN</a> have been audited multiple times.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-500 text-xl">✓</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Privacy-Friendly Jurisdiction:</strong> Choose VPNs based in countries with strong privacy laws (Switzerland, Sweden, Iceland) and outside Five/Nine/Fourteen Eyes surveillance alliances.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-500 text-xl">✓</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Modern Protocols:</strong> WireGuard should be available. OpenVPN is acceptable. Avoid PPTP and L2TP.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-500 text-xl">✓</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Kill Switch:</strong> Automatically blocks internet if VPN disconnects, preventing IP leaks.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-500 text-xl">✓</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Transparent Ownership:</strong> Avoid VPNs owned by data analytics companies (looking at you, Kape Technologies).
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Find Your Perfect VPN</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Answer 4 quick questions and we'll recommend the best VPN for your needs
