            Take the VPN Quiz →
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="faq" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="font-bold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">Are VPNs legal?</summary>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
              VPNs are legal in most countries including the US, UK, Canada, Australia, and most of Europe. However, they are restricted or banned in countries like China, Russia, Belarus, North Korea, Iran, and UAE. Even in countries where VPNs are legal, using them for illegal activities (piracy, hacking, etc.) is still illegal.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="font-bold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">Do VPNs slow down internet speed?</summary>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
              Quality VPNs typically reduce speeds by 5-15% due to encryption overhead and routing distance. The best VPNs like <a href="/reviews/mullvad" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Mullvad</a> with WireGuard show minimal speed loss (often under 5%). Free VPNs tend to be much slower due to server congestion.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="font-bold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">Can I use a free VPN?</summary>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
              Free VPNs typically make money by logging and selling your data, injecting ads, or limiting speeds/bandwidth severely. The only trustworthy free VPN is <a href="/reviews/protonvpn" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">ProtonVPN's free tier</a>, which has no data caps but limited server access. For serious privacy, invest in a paid VPN.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="font-bold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">Will a VPN hide me from the government?</summary>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
              VPNs provide privacy from mass surveillance but won't make you invisible to targeted investigations. If you're a person of interest, advanced techniques can potentially de-anonymize you. For maximum anonymity, combine a VPN with Tor. VPNs are best for protecting against dragnet surveillance, not targeted attacks.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-purple-50 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Ready to Get Started?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Compare the best privacy-focused VPNs based on real testing, not commissions
        </p>
